{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781914664897,"sessionID":"ses_11d9c6c00ffe6J1e6HYrGk22K5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"531508252","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Find build failure cause","prompt":"Read the following files in parallel and analyze what's causing a build failure:\n1. bench-targets/build-failure/src/config.mjs\n2. bench-targets/build-failure/build.mjs\n\nIdentify the root cause of the build configuration failure by comparing what these files expect versus what they're receiving. Report back the specific issues found.","subagent_type":"general"},"output":"<task id=\"ses_11d9c391effex42ASl9M9rRw5q\" state=\"completed\">\n<task_result>\n\n\n**Root cause: Property name mismatch**\n\n| Property | config.mjs provides | build.mjs expects |\n|----------|---------------------|-------------------|\n| Entry points array | `config.entries` | `config.entryPoints` |\n| Out directory | `config.outDir` | `config.outDir` ✓ |\n\nThe build.mjs file expects `entryPoints` but the config.mjs file exports `entries`. When the build script tries to access `config.entryPoints`, it returns `undefined`, which:\n1. Fails the `Array.isArray(undefined)` check\n2. Crashes when trying to access `entryPoints[0]`\n\n**Fix**: Change the config property from `entries` to `entryPoints` in config.mjs.\n</task_result>\n</task>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_11d9c6c00ffe6J1e6HYrGk22K5","sessionId":"ses_11d9c391effex42ASl9M9rRw5q","model":{"modelID":"qwen/qwen3.5-9b","providerID":"lmstudio"},"truncated":false},"title":"Find build failure cause","time":{"start":1781914650342,"end":1781914664894}},"id":"prt_ee263bd6e001cykZe0hpK2TndZ","sessionID":"ses_11d9c6c00ffe6J1e6HYrGk22K5","messageID":"msg_ee2639746001aNFAHOaPq9skTd"}}
